  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "The legal framework surrounding money laundering involves multiple levels of legislation and regulation designed to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes. Here are key elements:\n\n1. International Framework\n- UN Convention against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Egmont Group international cooperation standards\n\n2. National Legislation\n- Anti-Money Laundering (AML) laws\n- Bank Secrecy Act\n- Counter-Terrorism Financing regulations\n- Proceeds of Crime legislation\n\n3. Key Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Suspicious transaction reporting\n- Record-keeping obligations\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n- Transaction monitoring\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial crime enforcement agencies\n- Central banks\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Law enforcement departments\n\n5. Potential Penalties\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Business license revocation\n- Personal liability for executives\n\n6. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk assessment\n- Internal control systems\n- Staff training\n- Regular audits\n- Independent verification processes\n\nThe framework aims to prevent criminal organizations from integrating illegally obtained funds into legitimate financial systems.",
